description:
Overview

The Battle for Mars! With Superman having left the Kryptonian military to try to stop the war, General Zod needs a new Commander El – enter Supergirl! As Zod's army gets closer to Earth, the battlefield shifts to Mars where Superman must confront his cousin! Neither wants to fight, but both will do what they must for the sake of what they think is right! Meanwhile, Superboy knows what he must do to stop this war – even if it means becoming hated by both planets!
name: The Battle for Mars

description: At Veronica's house she has her servant looking for her leather handbag. After finding it she goes to the movies with Betty and Midge. The three pick a horror movie called "Night of the Killer Zombees". Later in the movie Midge is angered by the movie's non-scariness when a guy behind them angrees with her. While Midge and Betty think that he's trouble, but Veronica thinks he's cute. He then says his name is Nick St. Clair and he snuck into a movie. Later he asks Veronica to go on a ride in his motorcycle. Meanwhile at the Lodge Mansion everyone is wondering where Veronica is when she appears with Nick and said that Nick got into a fight with some bad boys.
name: Bad Boy Trouble

description: Monday at Riverdale High School , Archie asks Betty and Midge about their weekend when Betty tells Midge no to talk about Nick St. Clair. Later in the day Archie and Betty see Nick and Veronica.  Nick then introduces himself to Archie and calls him "Carrot-Top"  and forms a bad relation with him. Later in biology class Nick disturbs the class by making chicken noises and when the teacher asks who is making the noise, Archie tells him it was Nick and Nick is sent out. Later at lunch Nick and Archie argued when Betty left Nick followed a said he like her.
name: Bad Boy Trouble Part 2

description: At Betty's home Veronica is getting ready for her date with Nick. Nick then shows up and hits on Betty until Veronica shows up. Much later the next day Nick and Veronica finally show up. The next week at school Ms. Grundy assigns the class to write an essay. Later Nick forces Dilton to write his paper, but when he refuses Nick tries to hit him when Archie stops him.  Coach Clayton then proposes they fight in the school gym to settle the argument. The fight leaves Archie with a black eye and a broken jaw when Coach stops the fight and Nick says the fight isn't over.
name: Bad Boy Trouble Part 3

description: Spinning out of BRIGHTEST DAY, DC's new biweekly event begins here! Someone is targeting the old members of the defunct Justice League International. Now, surviving members Booster Gold, Captain Atom, Fire and Ice have to figure out what unseen mastermind is threatening to destroy the entire Super Hero community! There are no gray areas here – it's black and white and red with blood all over for this lost generation of Super Heroes as original JUSTICE LEAGUE INTERNATIONAL writer Keith Giffen is joined by superstar scribe Judd Winick (BATMAN, GREEN ARROW) for a new era in excitement !
name: Gone But Not Forgotten

description: Mon-El's final task affects the future of the entire universe! Plus, Brainiac 5 and R.E.B.E.L.S. leader Brainiac 2 confront their evil ancestor – the original Brainiac!

description: "What Happens in Vega..." part 2! In the wake of cosmic cataclysm, super-genius Vril Dox rebuilds his space police force L.E.G.I.O.N., his latest world-shaking move putting him right in the cross hairs of everyone across the Vega Sector. But they'll have to get in line behind the wrath of Blackfire!
name: What Happens In Vega... Part 2

description:
It's amazing how many comics fans who grew up admiring Spiderman, Batman, and Nick Fury still retain warm places in their hearts for Casper the Friendly Ghost. Now Dark Horse is delighted to participate in the revival of Casper, who remains among the most beloved of cartoon and comic book icons. Casper the Friendly Ghost made his first appearance as a star of Paramount's Famous Cartoons in 1947 and entered the comics in 1949. But after five issues, publisher St. John's gave up the title. That's when Harvey Comics stepped in, and where this book begins. Harvey breathed life into Casper, and from the very first issue, the cover designs, stories, and artwork-drawn by the same animators who worked on the cartoons-were a cut above.

Harvey Comics Classics Volume 1: Casper contains over 100 of Casper's very best stories, from the beginning of the Harvey series in 1952 through the classic years of the mid-1960s. The art is reproduced from crisp black-and-white printer's proofs and original artwork from the old Harvey archives, along with sixty four pages of color meticulously restored from the original comic books. The book includes a comprehensive introduction illustrated with historic memorabilia.
name: Casper the Friendly Ghost
